  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Global Learning Programme (England) Extension</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is an extension of CPNA81, linked to the Global Learning Programme (GLP) in England (for which Oxfam was a consortium partner).   The GLP is a five -year programme running from 2013&#x2013;2018. It aimed to support teachers to deliver effective teaching and learning about development and global issues at Key Stages 2 and 3 (pupils aged 8 to 14). The premise is that teachers who are more confident and able in global learning will adapt their teaching to incorporate global themes, and encourage whole -school change. This in turn will lead to enhanced global learning outcomes for pupils.   The GLP uses a network model to engage schools, where Expert Centres act as hubs to recruit and support teachers in local Partner Schools. The programme has a revised target to reach 7,500 schools (over the five years), a third of the schools in England. Teachers will receive training through attending twilight sessions in their clusters. Schools can also access funding for Continuous Professional Development (CPD) through accredited providers.   DEVA54 covers an extension period of activities taking place from the end of March to the end of July 2018. A payment schedule outlining the planned activities by Oxfam (and associated costs) is attached.</narrative>
  </description>
